pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Shoes plus socks; Waterproof gloves; Chemical-resistant apron when mixing or loading, cleaning up spills or equipment, or otherwise exposed to the concentrate.

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed. Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes or on clothing.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15 to 20 minutes; remove contact lenses after first 5 minutes then continue rinsing; call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice; have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow; do not induce vomiting unless told to do so; do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: If pesticide gets on skin, wash immediately with soap and water.
